series-2018-19-1213344|archive-date=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| link2            = The Masked Singer (American season 2)\n| timeslot2        = Wednesday 8:00&nbsp;p.m.\n| timeslot_length2 = 2\n| episodes2        = 13\n| start2           = {{Start date|2019|9|25}}\n| startrating2     = 8.03<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-premiere-helps-fox-to-dominate-prime-time-as-it-doubled-the-runner-up-network-in-adults-18-49/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''The Masked Singer'' Season Premiere Helps Fox to Dominate Prime Time as it Doubled the Runner-Up Network in Adults 18-49|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=September 27, 2019|website=Programming Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005182232/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-premiere-helps-fox-to-dominate-prime-time-as-it-doubled-the-runner-up-network-in-adults-18-49/|archive-date=October 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| end2             = {{End date|2019|12|18}}\n| endrating2       = 8.37<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-over-12-million-watch-impeachment-vote-coverage-across-various-cable-news-stations/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: Over 12 Million Watch Impeachment Vote Coverage Across Various Cable News Stations|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=December 19, 2019|website=Programming Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328034025/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-over-12-million-watch-impeachment-vote-coverage-across-various-cable-news-stations/|archive-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| season2          = 2019\u201320\n| season_length2   = 2\n| rank2            = \n| rank_length2     = 2\n| viewers2         = \n| viewers_length2  = 2\n| 18_49_rank2      = \n| 18_49_rank_length2 = 2\n| 18_49_rating2    = \n| 18_49_rating_length2 = 2\n\n| link3            = The Masked Singer (American season 3)\n| episodes3        = \n| start3           = {{Start date|2020|2|2}}\n| startrating3     = 23.78<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/sunday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-third-season-premiere-on-fox-generates-second-largest-total-audience-and-adults-18-49-delivery-for-a-super-bowl-lead-out-in-five-years/|title=Sunday Final Ratings: ''The Masked Singer'' Third Season Premiere on Fox Generates Second-Largest Total Audience and Adults 18-49 Delivery for a Super Bowl Lead-Out in Five Years|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=February 5, 2020|website=Programming Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211224755/https://programminginsider.com/sunday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-third-season-premiere-on-fox-generates-second-largest-total-audience-and-adults-18-49-delivery-for-a-super-bowl-lead-out-in-five-years/|archive-date=February 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| end3             = {{End date|2020|5|20}}<ref name=\"The Futon Critic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/masked-singer/listings/|title=''The Masked Singer'' Episode Listings|website=[[The Futon Critic]]|access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| endrating3       = \n| season3          = hide\n| rank3            = hide\n| viewers3         = hide\n| 18_49_rank3      = hide\n| 18_49_rating3    = hide\n}}\n</noinclude>\n''The Masked Singer'' premiered in January 2019 as the highest rated [[reality television|unscripted]] television series debut since ''[[The X Factor (American TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in 2011. Following three days of DVR viewing, the first episode's 18\u201349 rating grew by 30 percent\u2014the highest increase ever for a premiere in the show's genre.<ref>{{cite web|last=Holloway|first=Daniel|title=''The Masked Singer'' Scores Biggest Live+3 Lift Ever for Unscripted Series|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/masked-singer-ratings-1203101918/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125164644/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/masked-singer-ratings-1203101918/|archive-date=December 22, 2019|date=January 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Although initially dropping, ratings grew towards the end of the season, and the finale became the most watched episode.<ref name=\"ADW Sep 25\">{{cite web|last=Lynch|first=Jason|title=How Freshman Hit ''The Masked Singer'' Will Try to Avoid a Sophomore Slump|url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/masked-singer-season-2-what-to-expect/|website=[[Adweek]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926021058/https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/masked-singer-season-2-what-to-expect/|archive-date=September 26, 2019|date=September 25, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> According to [[Comscore]], the show had one of the highest viewer engagement levels of any television series during the week the finale aired.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=TV's Stickiest Shows|url=https://link.gale.com/apps/doc/A606540478/GPS|magazine=[[Broadcasting & Cable]]|via=[[Gale (publisher)|Gale In Context: Biography]]|date=March 18, 2019|url-access=subscription}}</ref> It concluded the [[2018\u201319 United States network television schedule|2018\u201319 television season]] as the highest rated new series among adults 18\u201349, averaging a 2.6 rating throughout all ten episodes,<ref name=\"S1AvgRatings\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ratings-broadcast-network-series-2018-19-1213344|title=2018-19 TV Season Ratings: 90 Percent of Veteran Broadcast Shows Fall|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=May 23, 2019|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617113702/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ratings-broadcast-network-series-2018-19-1213344|archive-date=June 17, 2019}}</ref> and as the highest rated entertainment series among teens, men 18\u201334, adults 18\u201334, and adults 18\u201349.<ref name=\"ADW Oct 20\">{{cite web|title=The 2019 TV Hot List: The Year's Biggest and Buzziest Shows, Networks and People|url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/the-2019-tv-hot-list-the-years-biggest-and-buzziest-shows-networks-and-people/4/|website=[[Adweek]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230042701/https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/the-2019-tv-hot-list-the-years-biggest-and-buzziest-shows-networks-and-people/4/|archive-date=December 30, 2019|date=October 20, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> The show was the first unscripted series to rank number-one in the genre in its first season since ''[[Joe Millionaire]]'' in 2003,<ref name=\"VAR Feb 19\">{{cite news|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=Who Is That Masked B-Lister?|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48002572/the-gazette/|work=[[Montreal Gazette]]|agency=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404200853/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48002572/the-gazette/|archive-date=April 4, 2020|date=February 19, 2019|url-status=live|via=[[Ancestry.com#Newspapers.com|Newspapers.com]]}}</ref> and was one of the reasons why Fox was the only network to gain viewers compared to the previous television season.<ref>{{cite news|last=Levin|first=Gary|title=Fox plots more 'toons, a ''9-1-1'' spinoff, the end of ''Empire'' and plenty of ''Masked Singer''|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/05/13/foxs-fall-schedule-adds-new-toon-wwe-wrestling-and-masked-singer/1184733001/|work=[[USA Today]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513172632/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/05/13/foxs-fall-schedule-adds-new-toon-wwe-wrestling-and-masked-singer/1184733001/|archive-date=April 10, 2020|date=May 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Ad Age]]'', the series was one of two non-[[National Football League|NFL]] programs to cost at least $200,000 per thirty seconds of advertising during the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule|2019\u201320 television season]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Adgate|first=Brad|title=TV Ad Rates (But Not Ad Revenue) Are Dropping|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bradadgate/2019/10/15/tv-ad-rates-but-not-ad-revenue-are-dropping/|website=[[Forbes]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408171217/https://www.forbes.com/sites/bradadgate/2019/10/15/tv-ad-rates-but-not-ad-revenue-are-dropping/|archive-date=April 8, 2020|date=October 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The second season premiered 17 percent lower than the previous but was similar to the first season's average.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thorne|first=Will|title=TV Ratings: ''The Masked Singer'' Easily Wins Wednesday|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-2-premiere-1203350350/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927145835/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-2-premiere-1203350350/|archive-date=September 27, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The finale's ratings also dropped compared to the first season, though the broadcast was up 20 percent in viewers from the previous week's episode.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|title=''The Masked Singer'' & ''Survivor'' Finales, ''Live In Front Of A Studio Audience'' Ratings Dip Amid Primetime Impeachment Vote|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/the-masked-singer-finale-ratings-survivor-winner-live-in-front-of-a-studio-audience-1202813754/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304071423/https://deadline.com/2019/12/the-masked-singer-finale-ratings-survivor-winner-live-in-front-of-a-studio-audience-1202813754/|archive-date=March 4, 2020|date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Deadline Hollywood]] cited the second season as a major reason why Fox\u2014for the first time in the network's history\u2014ranked number-one in fall entertainment programming,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|title=Fox Tops Fall Demo Ratings For First Time In Decade; NBC Snaps CBS' Total Viewers Streak|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/tv-ratings-fall-2019-fox-wins-nbc-the-masked-singer-sunday-night-football-1202817673/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104191044/https://deadline.com/2019/12/tv-ratings-fall-2019-fox-wins-nbc-the-masked-singer-sunday-night-football-1202817673/|archive-date=January 4, 2020|date=December 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and ''[[Adweek]]'' named the show the \"Hottest Reality/Competition Series\" of 2019.<ref name=\"ADW Oct 20\"/> The third season, which premiered as the [[Super Bowl LIV]] [[list of Super Bowl lead-out programs|lead-out program]], was viewed by over 23.7 million people. While the episode was watched by more than the previous lead-out, ''[[The World's Best]]'' (22.2 million), and Fox's most recent lead-out, 2017's ''[[24: Legacy]]'' (17.6 million), it was lower than the viewership of ''[[This Is Us]]'' (27 million) in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Adalian|first=Joseph|title=23 Million People Watched a Celebrity Pretend to Be a Robot on ''The Masked Singer''|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/the-masked-singer-super-bowl-ratings.html|website=[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311162320/https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/the-masked-singer-super-bowl-ratings.html|archive-date=March 11, 2020|date=February 3, 2020|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> During the latter half of the season which aired during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the series\u2014like others\u2014experienced viewership and 18\u201349 rating gains of 10\u201315 percent compared to the episodes that aired before the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thorne|first=Will|title=Network TV Sees a Ratings Revival Amid Coronavirus Outbreak, but Will It Last?|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/self-isolation-ratings-network-tv-1203545128/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411070014/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/self-isolation-ratings-network-tv-1203545128/|archive-date=April 11, 2020|date=March 26, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Porter|first=Rick|title=TV Long View: The Shows With the Biggest Quarantine Viewing Gains|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/60-minutes-blacklist-lead-quarantine-viewing-gains-1288507|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413011213/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/60-minutes-blacklist-lead-quarantine-viewing-gains-1288507|archive-date=April 13, 2020|date=April 4, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Excluding the third season's premiere following the Super Bowl, the show's two-hour broadcast on April 1 was the most watched since the first season's finale.<ref name=\"VAR Mar 26\">{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'': Gordon Ramsay Is First Confirmed Guest for Fox's ''After The Mask'' Post-Show (Exclusive)|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-gordon-ramsay-after-the-mask-1234580325/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415220047/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-gordon-ramsay-after-the-mask-1234580325/|archive-date=April 15, 2020|date=April 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nThe series has received generally unfavorable reviews from critics, though its costumes have been praised for their complexity.<ref>{{cite web |title=Critic Reviews for ''The Masked Singer'' |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-masked-singer/critic-reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\nKelly Lawler of ''[[USA Today]]'' attributed the series' success to its brilliant concept only and named the panel the worst in reality television history. She described Jeong as over-the-top, McCarthy Wahlberg as inexperienced, Scherzinger as dull, and Thicke as too serious.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lawler|first=Kelly|title=The 5 best (and 5 worst) reality-TV show judging panels of all time|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/02/25/reality-tv-judges-5-best-and-5-worst-panels-all-time-the-voice-american-idol-simon-cowell-rupaul/2937947002/|website=[[USA Today]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401114701/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/02/25/reality-tv-judges-5-best-and-5-worst-panels-all-time-the-voice-american-idol-simon-cowell-rupaul/2937947002/|archive-date=April 1, 2020|date=February 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, ''Variety''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s [[Caroline Framke]] felt the panelists gave worthless insights and that the show was boring due to the caliber of celebrities competing not living up to the hype the show promotes them as when they are unmasked.<ref>{{cite web|last=Framke|first=Caroline|author-link=Caroline Framke|title=TV Review: ''The Masked Singer''|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/reviews/the-masked-singer-review-fox-korea-1203096239/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406202742/https://variety.com/2018/tv/reviews/the-masked-singer-review-fox-korea-1203096239/|archive-date=April 6, 2019|date=December 28, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Kristen Baldwin and Joseph Longo also criticized them. The former felt the show was captivating but said the panelists were unfit to be critiquing singers and that they paid little attention to the clues or performances<ref>{{cite web|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen|title=Fox's ''The Masked Singer'': What the holy hell is this?|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2019/01/02/the-masked-singer-fox-recap/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920204236/https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2019/01/02/the-masked-singer-fox-recap/|archive-date=April 20, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and the latter thought that Cannon\u2014despite his experience\u2014was overshadowed by the presence and commentary of McCarthy Wahlberg. While Longo criticized Cannon for not interacting with the panelists, he was pleasantly surprised by the quality of singing on the show and thought the performances were more interesting than listening to the panelists' guesses.<ref name=\"EW Jan 1\"/> [[Matt Zoller Seitz]] of ''Vulture'' lambasted the presence of McCarthy Wahlberg as a panelist (referring to her [[Jenny McCarthy#Autism activism and views on vaccines|prominent]] [[vaccine hesitancy|anti-vaccine]] views) but praised her chemistry with the rest of the panel. He criticized the way the show's producers edit their guesses, stating they should cut out repetitive comments more often.<ref>{{cite web|last=Seitz|first=Matt Zoller|author-link=Matt Zoller Seitz|title=How Is ''The Masked Singer'' Real?|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-masked-singer-season-2-review.html|website=Vulture|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218162823/https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-masked-singer-season-2-review.html|archive-date=December 18, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Others from ''Vulture'' also derided the editing as awkward and felt the panelists were mindless and unfunny, condemning them for spoiling the show's innovative concept with distracting statements. However, they were impressed by the costumes, describing the Egg as timeless, the Butterfly as gorgeous, and the Rottweiler as a badass.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wright|first=Megh|title=Egg Was Too Pure for This Terrible World|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/goodbye-egg.html|website=Vulture|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926201418/https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/goodbye-egg.html|archive-date=September 26, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=VanArendonk|first=Kathryn|title=''The Masked Singer'' Is a Reality-TV Fever Dream|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|website=Vulture|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225230817/https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|archive-date=December 25, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\n[[File:American Idol logo.svg|thumb|upright=1|alt=refer to caption|One critic contrasted the series' positivity with the often negative nature of other reality shows such as ''[[American Idol]]'' while another (contrary to most) compared the panelists favorably to the original ''Idol'' judges.]]\nAfter attended a taping of the show, Kayla Keegan of ''[[Good Housekeeping]]'' said she appreciated the detailing of the costumes and praised Toybina's skill in designing them.<ref name=\"GH Feb 6\"/> The ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' also commended Toybina's costumes; Yvonne Villarreal said they were showstopping and helped make the show successful.<ref name=\"LA Feb 6\"/> Malcolm Venable of ''[[TV Guide]]'' thought the costumes were fantastic but described the performers' singing abilities as lackluster and the panelists' guesses as absurd.<ref>{{cite web|last=Venable|first=Malcolm|title=Is ''The Masked Singer'' Terrible, or Am I Just Old and Cranky?|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-masked-singer-review/|website=[[TV Guide]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914015641/https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-masked-singer-review/|archive-date=September 14, 2019|date=December 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Megan Garber of ''[[The Atlantic]]'' compared the series' format to that of [[Police procedural|crime procedural]] ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' due to its mystery elements while [[CNN]]'s Brian Lowry felt the show's [[novelty]] would soon fade away because it is gimmicky.<ref name=\"ATL Feb 28\">{{cite web|last=Garber|first=Megan|title=''The Masked Singer'' Lets You In on the Scam|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/02/masked-singer-finale-what-show-really-reveals/583882/|website=[[The Atlantic]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308121421/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/02/masked-singer-finale-what-show-really-reveals/583882/|archive-date=March 8, 2020|date=February 28, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=limited}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lowry|first=Brian|title=''Titan Games'', ''Masked Singer'' launch hunt for next reality hit|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/31/entertainment/titan-games-masked-singer-reality-tv/index.html|website=[[CNN]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111064738/https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/31/entertainment/titan-games-masked-singer-reality-tv/index.html|archive-date=January 11, 2019|date=December 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>. Writing for ''[[The Washington Post]]'', Emily Yahr described the show as crazy but said Cannon was perfect as host, noting his years of experience in the same role on ''[[America's Got Talent]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yahr|first=Emily|title=Yes, that was real life: ''The Masked Singer'' premiered and was even weirder than you imagined|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|website=Vulture|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225230817/https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|archive-date=December 25, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Conversely, ''[[The Globe and Mail]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s [[John Doyle (critic)|John Doyle]] called Cannon inarticulate and described the panelists as [[Camp (style)|cheesy]] and irrelevant. He characterized the show as a wacky and dumb version of [[Charades]] but acknowledged that it is popular because of its simplicity. Doyle cited the series as an example of a cultural shift in the United States away from the competitive and often exploitative nature of shows such as ''[[American Idol]]'' towards a higher level of positivity among reality television series.<ref>{{cite web|last=Doyle|first=John|author-link=John Doyle (critic)|title=Dumb simplicity: Why ''The Masked Singer'' is a massive TV hit|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-dumb-simplicity-why-the-masked-singer-is-a-massive-tv-hit/|website=[[The Globe and Mail]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218163655/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-dumb-simplicity-why-the-masked-singer-is-a-massive-tv-hit/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|date=November 4, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Daniel D'Addario of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' described the show as relaxing and refreshing, calling it a return to form for television as the series possesses the now-rare ability to uplift and unite people. He commended the show's panelists, comparing them to the original ''American Idol'' judges as non-experts in their fields due to their common, implausible A-list celebrity guesses. He also praised the show's platform for allowing celebrities to express themselves freely even if they are not professional singers.<ref>{{cite web|last=D'Addario|first=Daniel|title=In Praise of ''The Masked Singer'', TV's Last Uniter (Column)|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/columns/masked-singer-super-bowl-1203485315/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210183913/https://variety.com/2020/tv/columns/masked-singer-super-bowl-1203485315/|archive-date=February 10, 2020|date=February 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Cultural impact===\nThe series is discussed on numerous [[podcast|podcasts]] and has generated its own [[Reddit#Subreddit|thread]] on [[Reddit]] where avid fans of the show extensively analyze the clues presented during an episode in an attempt to decode them.<ref name=\"BB Jan 31\"/><ref name=\"ATL Feb 28\"/> They have also replicated many of the series' costumes, including Peacock, Thingamajig, and Ice Cream, to wear on [[Halloween]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Yang|first=Rach|title=Best fan-made ''Masked Singer'' Halloween costumes: Lions, Peacocks, and Thingamajigs, oh my!|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/10/30/best-fan-made-masked-singer-halloween-costumes/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=October 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218093623/https://ew.com/tv/2019/10/30/best-fan-made-masked-singer-halloween-costumes/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2019, students at the [[Fashion Institute of Design & Merchandising]] college in California (of which Toybina is a graduate) were tasked with designing their own ''Masked Singer'' costume concepts as part of an assignment.<ref>{{cite web|title=''The Masked Singer'' Costume Designer Marina Toybina Reviews Student Designs on LA Campus|url=https://fidm.edu/en/majors/film+and+tv+costume+design/experience/latest+news/The+Masked+Singer+Costume+Designer+Marina+Toybina+Reviews+Student+Designs+on+LA+Campus|website=[[Fashion Institute of Design & Merchandising]]|date=December 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301162233/https://fidm.edu/en/majors/film+and+tv+costume+design/experience/latest+news/The+Masked+Singer+Costume+Designer+Marina+Toybina+Reviews+Student+Designs+on+LA+Campus|archive-date=March 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe show was the first in the [[Masked Singer|''Masked Singer'' franchise]] to air outside of Asia and its success has been attributed to subsequent local adaptations. The producers of the [[The Masked Singer (British TV series)|British series]] said they were inspired to adapt the format after watching the American version.<ref name=\"GH Feb 6\"/><ref name=\"THR Jan 2\"/> Wade has described a shift in the way new shows are [[sales presentation|pitched]] since the series premiered, noting there is an increased openness to new ideas. He also said the heads of almost all television networks thanked him for the series giving them a \"[[blank cheque|carte blanche]]\" to take new programming risks.<ref name=\"VAR Feb 19\"/> Michael Schneider of ''Variety'' said the show has revitalized reality television in the United States. The revivals of ''[[Paradise Hotel]]'' and ''[[Temptation Island (TV series)|Temptation Island]]'' by Fox and [[USA Network]], respectively, have been credited to the show's success, as have the American adaptations of ''[[Love Island (American TV series)|Love Island]]'' and ''[[I Can See Your Voice (American game show)|I Can See Your Voice]]''.<ref name=\"VAR Feb 19\"/> The show has also been credited with reinvigorating the costume genre of television. Interest in adapting other costume-centered series such as ''[[Wild Things (game show)|Wild Things]]'' and ''[[Sexy Beasts]]'' has increased around the world since the show premiered.<ref name=\"TBI Apr 5\"/>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|+ Awards and nominations\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11%;\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2%;\"| Year{{efn|Indicates the year of the ceremony.}}\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2%;\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Costume Designers Guild#Costume Designers Guild Awards|Costume Designers Guild Awards]]\n| [[Costume Designers Guild Awards 2019|2020]]\n| Excellence in Variety, Reality-Competition, Live Television\n| Marina Toybina (for \"Season Finale: And The Winner Takes It All and Takes It Off\")\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref name=\"CAG 2020\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Creative Arts Emmy Award|Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| [[71st Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards|2019]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Costumes for a Variety, Nonfiction, or Reality Programming|Outstanding Costumes for a Variety, Nonfiction, or Reality Programming]]\n| Marina Toybina, Grainne O'Sullivan (for \"Season Finale: The Final Mask is Lifted\")\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref name=\"Emmy 2019\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Critics' Choice Real TV Awards]]\n| [[1st Critics' Choice Real TV Awards|2019]]\n| Competition Series: Talent/Variety\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Montgomery|first=Daniel|title=Winners of the Inaugural Critics' Choice Real TV Awards|url=http://www.criticschoice.com/critics-choice-real-tv-awards/|publisher=[[Broadcast Film Critics Association]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918170057/http://www.criticschoice.com/critics-choice-real-tv-awards/|archive-date=September 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Gold Derby]] TV Awards\n| 2019\n| Competition Program\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last1=Montgomery|first1=Daniel|last2=Dixon|first2=Marcus James|last3=Beachum|first3=Chris|last4=Eng|first4=Joyce|last5=Sheehan|first5=Paul|last6=Wloszczyna|first6=Susan|title=Gold Derby TV Awards winners 2019: ''Game of Thrones'' and ''Fleabag'' rule, but voters spread the wealth|url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/gold-derby-tv-awards-winners-2019-game-of-thrones-fleabag-news/|website=[[Gold Derby]]|date=September 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406001043/https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/gold-derby-tv-awards-winners-2019-game-of-thrones-fleabag-news/|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2020 Kids' Choice Awards|TBA]]\n| Favorite Reality Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{pending}}\n| style=text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/avengers-end-game-leads-nickelodeons-kids-choice-awards-nominations-billie-eilish-taylor-swift-chance-the-rapper-full-list-1202859259/|title=''Avengers: Endgame'' Leads Nickelodeon's Kids' Choice Awards Nominations; Chance The Rapper Set As Host|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Denise Petski|date=February 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313113934/https://deadline.com/2020/02/avengers-end-game-leads-nickelodeons-kids-choice-awards-nominations-billie-eilish-taylor-swift-chance-the-rapper-full-list-1202859259/|archive-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite TV Host\n| [[Nick Cannon]]\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| [[2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards|2019]]\n| Best Host\n| Nick Cannon\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Bell|first=Crystal|title=2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards Winners: See the Full List|url=https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|website=[[MTV]]|date=June 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620221134/https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[45th People's Choice Awards|2019]]\n| The Competition Show of 2019\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Here Are All the 2019 E! People's Choice Awards Winners|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8543205/2019-peoples-choice-awards-winners|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402041818/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8543205/2019-peoples-choice-awards-winners|archive-date=April 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| The Competition Contestant of 2019\n| [[T-Pain]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award|Producers Guild of America Awards]]\n| [[31st Producers Guild of America Awards|2020]]\n| Outstanding Producer of Game & Competition Television \n| Craig Plestis, Izzie Pick Ibarra, Nikki Varhely-Gillingham, Rosie Seitchik, Stacey Thomas-Muir, Nick Cannon, Ashley Sylvester, Lindsay Tuggle, Pete Cooksley, Chelsea Candelaria, Anne Chanthavong, Zo\u00eb Ritchken, Deena Katz, Erin Brady, Jeff Kmiotek, Lexi Shoemaker\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 PGA Awards Winners|url=https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|website=[[Producers Guild of America]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307135545/https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|archive-date=March 7, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Brunico Communications|Realscreen Awards]]\n| 2020\n| Talent & Studio-Based Competition\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 Winners & Nominees|url=https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|website=Realscreen|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405233615/https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[11th Shorty Awards|2019]]\n| Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps \n| ''The Masked Singer'' Social Hub\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps|url=https://shortyawards.com/category/11th/entertainment-apps|website=[[Shorty Awards]]|date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/poEjN|archive-date=April 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n| Choice Reality TV Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2019 Teen Choice Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=August 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215073036/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|archive-date=February 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Spin-offs==\n===''The Masked Singer: After the Mask''===\n[[File:Masked-singer-after-the-mask.png|upright=1|thumb|Logo for the aftershow.|alt=refer to caption]]\nOn April 8, 2020, Fox announced that Cannon will host an [[aftershow]] of the series titled ''The Masked Singer: After the Mask'' on Wednesdays at 9:00 p.m. for four weeks starting on April 22. He will host the show from his house and discuss the outcome of the preceding episode with celebrity guests appearing remotely.<ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' After-Show, Hosted by Nick Cannon, to Launch on Fox|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-after-the-mask-nick-cannon-fox-1234574761/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Roots|first=Kimberly|title=''The Masked Singer'' to Get Aftershow|url=https://tvline.com/2020/04/08/the-masked-singer-aftershow-nick-cannon-season-3-fox/|website=[[TVLine]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> In the first episode, [[Kelly Osbourne]], [[JoJo Siwa]], Jeong, and McHale are all set to appear as guests, along with the eliminated celebrity with a performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/masked-singer-aftershow-after-the-mask-jojo-siwa-kelly-osbourne/|title=''Masked Singer'' Sets Alums Kelly Osbourne, JoJo Siwa as Guests for First-Ever Aftershow (Exclusive)|date=April 16, 2020|website=[[TheWrap]]|url-access=registration}}</ref> In the second episode, Ramsay is set to appear as a guest.<ref name=\"VAR Mar 26\"/>\n<!--\n{{Television episode ratings |width=85\n| show_timeslot = y\n\n| refs_col = y\n\n| title1     = After the Mask: The Mother Of All Final Face Offs, Part 2\n| date1      = April 22, 2020\n| timeslot1  = Wednesday 9:00 p.m.\n| timeslot_length1 = 4\n| rs1        = \n| viewers1   = \n| dvr1       = \n| dvrv1      = \n| total1     = \n| totalv1    = \n| ref1       = \n\n| title2     = After the Mask: The Battle of The Sixes: The Final 6\n| date2      = April 29, 2020\n| rs2        = \n| viewers2   = \n| dvr2       = \n| dvrv2      = \n| total2     = \n| totalv2    = \n| ref2       = \n\n| title3     = After the Mask: A Quarter Mask Crisis: The Quarter Finals\n| date3      = May 6, 2020\n| rs3        = \n| viewers3   = \n| dvr3       = \n| dvrv3      = \n| total3     = \n| totalv3    = \n| ref3       = \n\n| title4     = \n| date4      = May 13, 2020\n| rs4        = \n| viewers4   = \n| dvr4       = \n| dvrv4      = \n| total4     = \n| totalv4    = \n| ref4       = \n}} -->\n\n===''The Masked Dancer''===\nOn January 7, 2020, at the winter [[Television Critics Association]] press tour, Fox Alternative Entertainment and [[Warner Bros. Television]] announced that they had ordered a spin-off series, ''The Masked Dancer'', with [[Ellen DeGeneres]] as executive producer. DeGeneres had previously conducted ''The Masked Dancer'' as a recurring segment on her syndicated [[talk show]] ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' as a self-admitted parody of ''The Masked Singer''. She stated that the show was \"gonna be just as fun and suspenseful, but with a lot more [[krumping]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/the-masked-dancer-fox-partners-with-ellen-degeneres-on-the-masked-singer-spin-off-1202823169/|title=''The Masked Dancer'': Fox Partners With Ellen DeGeneres On ''The Masked Singer'' Spinoff \u2013 TCA|last=White|first=Peter|date=January 7, 2020|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/pug-almost-passes-out-playing-ellen-degeneres-latest-masked-singer-ripoff-video/|title=A Pug Almost Passes Out Playing Ellen DeGeneres' Latest ''Masked Dancer''|date=February 18, 2019|website=[[TheWrap]]|url-access=registration}}</ref> The series was expected to debut in summer 2020, however, due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]], production has not yet begun.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/a-puzzle-all-pieces-broadcast-networks-scramble-program-an-uncertain-future-1288828|title=A Puzzle Without All the Pieces: Broadcast Networks Scramble to Program an Uncertain Future|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=April 7, 2020|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\n==Other media==\nOn February 12, 2020, it was announced that the show would be getting a live national tour with shows in over forty-five cities. Beginning at the [[Fox Theatre (Detroit)|Fox Theatre]] in [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]] on May 28, 2020, the tour will feature two celebrity hosts as well as a local mystery celebrity who is unmasked at the end of each show.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200212005953/en/MASKED-SINGER-Unveils-45-City-U.S.-National|title=''The Masked Singer'' Unveils 45+ City U.S. National Tour|via=[[Business Wire]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' Announces Nationwide Concert Tour This Summer|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/masked-singer-concert-tour-summer-1203502739/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref> The series has an online store where hoodies, coffee mugs, and phone cases, among others using the show's branding, are available for purchase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://maskedsingershop.com/|website=The Masked Singer Shop|title=The Masked Singer Merchandise|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref> On February 24, 2020, toy manufacturer Jazwares announced they had partnered with Fox to release a ''Masked Singer''-inspired karaoke microphone under their \"First Act\" brand. The microphone will include a voice-changing feature and be sold at retail later in the year.<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer'' |date=February 24, 2020|publisher=Jazwares|via=[[PR Newswire]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225165959/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|archive-date=February 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|title=NY Toy Fair: Jazwares Unveils UFC, ''The Masked Singer'', ''Fortnite'' and All Elite Wrestling Toys|date=February 24, 2020|website=License Global|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410063545/https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[The World's Best ]]''<br />[[Super Bowl LIII|2019]]\n|list=[[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|Super Bowl lead-out program]]<br />''The Masked Singer''<br />[[Super Bowl LIV|2020]]\n|next=TBA\n}}\n\n{{The Masked Singer (American TV series)}}\n{{Masked Singer series}}\n{{FOXNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Masked Singer, The}}\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2010s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American game shows]]\n[[Category:2020s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American game shows]]\n[